headline: Jefferson Health goes out of network for Cigna commercial members following contract spat
summary: The Philadelphia-area system and major insurer have failed to reach a new agreement on payment rates, but are still continuing negotiations.

headline: The Cigna Group Completes Sale of Medicare Businesses to HCSC
summary: Global health company The Cigna Group (NYSE: CI) today announced the successful completion of the sale of its Medicare Advantage, Cigna Supplemental Benefits, Medicare Part D, and CareAllies businesses to Health Care Service Corporation (HCSC). The divestment of these assets streamlines The Cigna Group's portfolio and enables it to drive further innovation to support customers.
